## Inline directives
@divider

Inline directives do not required a closing tag, can be used within a line of text. Just calling `@name` will generate the directive's output.

```mq
@card
  
  ## Title
  @divider    <--- this is an inline directive
  There's now a divider between the title and me! @sparkle
@end card
```
@end card

@card
  ##* Preview
  @divider

    This card now contains two inline directives:

    @card
      
      ##* Title
      @divider
      There's now a divider between the title and me! @sparkle
    @end card

@end card

@end row

