@card
## Modifiers and labels
@divider

Modifiers are the `.tokens` after the directive name. Some directives also use the trailing label.

- `@callout .warn`
- `@dropdown .open "Windows Users"`
- `@product-card .featured Starter`
- `@step 4`
- `@step reset:1`
@end card


## Built-in directives
@divider

The core built-ins live in `template/directives/builtins.js`.

@row
@card
## Layout and structure
@divider

- `@container`: structural wrapper that does not emit its own element and resets step numbering for its children
- `@row`: responsive grid based on the number of block directive children
- `@column`: vertical stack inside a row
- `@section`: section wrapper with `.mods` mapped to CSS classes
- `@hero`: prominent section wrapper with `.mods` mapped to CSS classes
- `@card`: padded surface block with `.mods` mapped to CSS classes
@end card

@card
## Content and flow
@divider

- `@callout [.variant]`: note block, defaulting to `info`
- `@stat`: value plus label pair extracted from the rendered children
- `@step [number|*|reset:n]`: numbered process item with optional manual control
- `@divider`: the only built-in inline directive, rendered as a divider line

`@callout` knows these built-in variants: `info`, `warn`, `danger`, `ok`, `primary`, `secondary`, `tertiary`.
@end card
@end row

@row
@card
## Diagnostics
@divider

Some built-ins also validate their input:

- `@row` warns if it has no block directive children
- `@callout` warns if you use an unknown variant

Those checks come from the directive definition itself, not from a hard-coded parser rule.
@end card

@card
## Step notes
@divider

`@step` supports a few useful forms:

- `@step`: automatic numbering
- `@step 4`: force this step to show `4`
- `@step *`: show `*` instead of a number
- `@step reset:1`: reset the sequence when used inside a container flow
@end card
@end row

## Built-in composition
@divider

@row
@card
```mq
@container
  @callout .info
  Directives are just HTML generators with friendlier authoring syntax.
  @end callout

  @row
    @card
      ## Cards
      Great for grouped content.
    @end card

    @card
      ## Layout
      `@row` turns sibling blocks into a grid.
    @end card
  @end row

  @step
  Write the source.
  @end step

  @step
  Let Marque render the HTML.
  @end step
@end container
```
@end card

@card
@container
  @callout .info
  Directives are just HTML generators with friendlier authoring syntax.
  @end callout

  @row
    @card
      ## Cards
      Great for grouped content.
    @end card

    @card
      ## Layout
      `@row` turns sibling blocks into a grid.
    @end card
  @end row

  @step
  Write the source.
  @end step

  @step
  Let Marque render the HTML.
  @end step
@end container
@end card
@end row

## Starter project directives
@divider

The starter site also ships with example project directives in `template/directives/`. These are normal directives loaded from files, not parser special cases, so you can replace or delete them freely.

@row
@card
## `@dropdown`
@divider
- `type`: block
- `path`: `directives/dropdown.js`
- `description`: collapsible block that can be toggled open and closed. Starts in `closed` state by default.
- `param`: `.open`/`.expanded`/`.default-open` create the dropdown in the open state
- `param`: `.disable-cache` disables the caching behaviour
- `note`: the `@dropdown` directive has built-in caching, and remembers its open/closed state

```mq
@dropdown .open "Open by default"
You can see me!
@end dropdown

@dropdown "Closed by default"
Hello!
@end dropdown
```
@end card

@card
##* Preview
@divider

@dropdown .open "Open by default"
Use `marque serve .`
@end dropdown

@dropdown "Closed by default"
Hello!
@end dropdown

@divider

@callout .info
Try opening the "Closed by default" dropdown and refreshing the page. It will remember that you opened it and remain open.
@end card
@end row

@row
@card
## `@product-card`
@divider

- block directive rendered as a `<product-card>` element
- the first modifier becomes the `variant` attribute
- the trailing label becomes the `title` attribute

```mq
@product-card .featured Starter
## Fast setup
Copy the starter and change the theme later.
@end product-card
```
@end card

@card
##* Preview
@divider

@product-card .featured Starter
## Fast setup
Copy the starter and change the theme later.
@end product-card
@end card
@end row

@row
@card
## `@toc`
@divider

`summary.js` registers the `@toc` directive.

- `@toc` or `@toc .page` summarizes the current page
- `@toc .scoped` or `@toc .local` summarizes the previous block only
- `@toc .global` is an alias for page mode
- an optional label changes the panel title

```mq
@card
  ## Scoped summary demo
  ### Install
  ### Theme
@end card

@toc .scoped "Summary"
```
@end card

@card
##* Preview
@divider

@card
## Scoped summary demo
### Install
Add headings to the previous block.
### Theme
`@toc .scoped` only reads that block.
@end card

@toc .scoped "Summary"
@end card
@end row

@row
@card
## Decorative starters
@divider

The starter also ships with two tiny decorative directives:

- `@sparkle`: inline animated star
- `@spotlight`: decorative spotlight block

These are examples of how small a directive can be.
@end card

@card
